<1ST_LINE>r a PM-GatorBattle     06-27 0247</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Gator Battle,0255</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Youth Beats Alligator To Death in Michigan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIDLAND, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 3-foot-long alligator that turned up in
a dog's kennel was beaten to death by a 12-year-old boy wielding a
tennis racket as the reptile struggled with his Doberman pinscher.
   ``It freaked me out. It was so strong,'' said Ben Clifton. ``I
hit it in the head 15, 20 times and it still wasn't dead.''
   Ben said he was watching a ``Godzilla'' movie on television
Friday when he heard his dog, Fawn, barking and growling.
   He found both animals inside the Doberman's kennel, with Fawn's
teeth clenched on the back of the gator's neck and the reptile's
teeth around the dog's collar.
   Ben ran back inside for a weapon. ``I grabbed the closest thing
... a tennis racket.''
   Ben ignored Fawn's efforts to keep him out of the kennel, and
struck the alligator. It let go of the dog and approached the boy,
who hit it until it stopped snapping. Fawn was not seriously hurt.
   Although owning a live alligator is illegal, a fraternity member
at Northwood Institute student brought the beast to Midland after a
spring break trip to Florida, according to student Bill Sulkanen.
   The student sold the gator to a Midland man when he went home
for the summer, another man who refused to give his name told the
Midland Daily News. The new owner apparently released the alligator
after leaving Midland about three weeks ago, the newspaper said.
</TEXT>
