<HEAD>Rudolf Nureyev's 50th Celebrated at the Met Gala</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rudolf Nureyev will belatedly celebrate his 50th
birthday tonight in the company of fellow ballet greats such as
Dame Margot Fonteyn and some not-so-greats, such as the prima
ballerina Miss Piggy of ``Swine Lake'' fame.
   The Paris Opera Ballet, directed by Nureyev since 1983, will
perform at the Metropolitan Opera House in honor of the dancer's
birthday, albeit three months and 10 days after he reached half a
century.
   Nureyev's impact was first felt in 1961, when he bolted from the
Kirov Ballet, a Soviet company visiting Paris at the time, and
defected.
   Nureyev is credited with breaking molds within tradition and
blending a sensuality with disciplined virtuosity.
