<HEAD>Radio Reports 26 Killed In Train-Bus Wreck Near Havana</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A train and bus collision east of Havana killed 26
people, most of them youths, and left 80 other people injured,
Cuba's state-run radio reported today.
   The crash occurred Saturday, and more than half of those injured
were in serious condition, according to a broadcast monitored here.
Most of those killed were between 12 and 19, the radio reported.
   No cause was given for the accident, which occurred along the
Barrera Highway in the city of Guanabacoa, the destination of the
bus from Megano Beach. Guanabacoa is about 10 miles east of Havana.
   All but five of the victims' remains have been identified, the
report said. It did not list any names.
   It was the second transportation tragedy in Cuba in a week.
   A collision between a bus and a tractor-trailer along Cuba's
main highway left 10 people dead and 21 injured, a Havana radio
station reported Friday. That wreck occurred when the bus driver
was blinded by lights of oncoming traffic near Jaguey Grande in the
Matanzas province.
