<HEAD>Officials Say Six Dead After Natural Gas Explosion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAIORI, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A natural gas explosion early today
destroyed a three-story building and killed six people, including
four members of one family, in this tourist village near Naples,
authorities said.
   Firemen rescued Anna Di Somma, 14, but said her parents and two
teen-age brothers died in the apartment building blast. The girl
was listed in good condition at a local hospital with a broken hip
and leg.
   Officials did not elaborate on the cause of the explosion.
   Authorities said they had recovered the bodies of Luis Carlo
Rossi, 33, and Carlo Ingravalle, 27, who shared one of the two
apartments destroyed by the blast.
   Firemen also recovered the body of Gerardo Di Somma, 46.
However, officials said his wife, Maria Rosaria Masolli, and their
two sons, Antonio Di Somma, 19, and Raimondo Di Somma, 17, were
still buried under the ruble.
   Officials said the bodies had been located, but that efforts to
recover them had been hampered because of fears that a portion of
the building still standing might collapse.
</TEXT>
