<HEAD>Italian Police Seize 123 Pounds of Heroin, 13 Arrested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILAN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police seized 123 pounds of heroin smuggled
into Italy from Turkey in meat trucks and arrested 13 people on
drug trafficking charges, investigators said Monday.
   Police estimated the street value of the heroin at $58.3 million.
   Thirteen people _ including two Yugoslavs, one Turk and one
Austrian _ were arrested and charged with drug possession and
trafficking.
   Most of the heroin was smuggled into Italy through Yugoslavia
and Austria aboard Turkish trucks transporting meat.
   Earlier searches of apartments in Italy of alleged ring members
led to the seizure of several pounds of heroin, nearly seven pounds
of cocaine and about 3 million lire (about $250,000) in cash.
</TEXT>
