<HEAD>11 Death Row Criminals Shot by Firing Squad</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ACCRA, Ghana (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eleven convicted armed robbers were escorted
from prison death row Monday and executed by a firing squad, the
government said.
   The prisoners were convicted in the past three years by a
special National Public Tribunal for armed robberies, a capital
crime in this West African nation.
   There were no immediate details of who was executed and for what
specific crimes. The government statement said only that in two of
the robberies for which prisoners were shot, foreign nationals had
been assaulted and robbed.
