<HEAD>30 Killed as Bus Swerves Off Highway to Avoid Hitting Goat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A crowded bus swerved to avoid hitting a
goat and toppled into a ravine on Monday, killing at least 30
people, according to a news report.
   The accident occurred in Bihar state near the town of Munger,
626 miles southeast of New Delhi, the United News of India reported.
   Unidentified police sources in Munger told the news agency that
the driver lost control of the bus when he tried to drive around a
goat that wandered onto the highway. The driver was unhurt but fled
the accident scene because he feared being arrested, the sources
said.
