<TEXT>
   Population, city: 425,022, 1980 census.
   Black population, city: 67 percent.
   Population, 18-county metro area, 1980 census: 2,138,231.
   Estimated population, metro, 1986: 2.5 million.
   Black population, metro area: 25 percent.
   Homeless population, city: 7,000-10,000, estimated.
   Projected population, metro, year 2000: 3 million.
   Median age, metro: 29 years.
   ``Baby boomers'': 36 percent.
   Atlanta natives: 41 percent.
   Male-female ratio: 93-100.
   Median education: 12.6 years.
