   Living below poverty level, city: 27.5 percent, 1980 census.
   Typical metro home price: $110,333.
   Largest employment sector, 1986: Service industries, 80 percent.
   Largest employer, metro Atlanta: Delta Air Lines, 19,500.
   Number of conventions, 1987: 1,617.
   Convention attendance, 1987: 1.6 million.
</TEXT>
