   Professional sports championships: One, 1968 Atlanta Chiefs,
soccer.
   Smallest Atlanta Braves baseball crowd: 737, Sept. 8, 1975, vs.
Houston.
   Original city name: Terminus.
   Number of streets somehow named ``Peachtree'': at least 34.
   Height of IBM Tower, city's tallest building: 825 feet.
