<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices declined broadly today as traders
cashed in on the market's recent gains.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, which rose 38.94 points
last week and reached its highest levels of the year, dropped back
8.36 to 2,134.60 in the first half hour of trading.
   Losers outnumbered gainers by more than 2 to 1 in the early
