down and 444 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 45.16 million shares as of 10
a.m. on Wall Street.
   The dollar was strong in early foreign-exchange activity today.
But that failed to inspire bond traders.
   Prices of long-term government bonds, which move in the opposite
direction from interest rates, fell about $5 for each $1,000 in
face value.
   Stocks came under similar light pressure amid some doubts that
the recent rally in the dollar would last much longer.
   Fort Howard Paper climbed 3] to 53. A group including top
executives of the company agreed to buy it out for $53 a share.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks fell
.74 to 153.82. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was down 1.12 at 307.37.
