<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Australia-CoalStrike     06-27 0123</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Australia-Coal Strike,0128</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Striking Coal Miners Return To Work</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Striking Australian coal miners
returned to work Monday, ending a national walkout that lasted more
than a week.
   Some of the 30,000 miners were on strike for 10 days protesting
changes in working conditions proposed by coal companies to keep
the mines working longer hours each week and more days each year.
   The proposed changes would include the introduction of
seven-day, 52-week rosters and changes to annual leave conditions.
A coal industry tribunal is currently considering the proposals.
   John Maitland, president of the Australian Miners' Federation,
said even though miners returned further job actions were possible
while the tribunal considered the matter.
   Australia is the world's biggest coal exporter.
</TEXT>
