<2ND_LINE>BC-Nynex-AGS,0194</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Nynex To Buy Portion Of AGS For $271 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nynex Corp. has signed a definitive agreement to
buy the services and software business of AGS Computers Inc. for
$271 million, the companies said Monday.
   As previously announced, AGS will cease to exist after
completion of the deal. Its shareholders will receive $21 in cash
for each share of AGS common stock. They will also receive, in a
one-for-one swap, shares of stock in AGS's subsidiary, Microamerica
Inc., a distributor of microcomputers and software.
   Microamerica will become a separate company. A special meeting
of AGS shareholders, who must approve the deal, is tentatively
scheduled for the early fall.
   The portion of AGS being bought by Nynex accounted for $190
million of AGS's 1987 revenue of $496 million and accounted for $21
million out of the company's $34 million in profits before holding
company expenses and financial expenses, Joseph Abrams, AGS's
president, said in an interview.
   AGS has headquarters in Mountainside, N.J. Nynex is the regional
Bell holding company for New York and New England and is based in
White Plains, N.Y.
</TEXT>
