<2ND_LINE>BC-Macmillan-Bass,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hearing Rescheduled in Bass Bid To Halt Macmillan Restructuring</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hearing in the Robert M. Bass Group's request
to halt publishing giant Macmillan Inc.'s planned restructuring has
been delayed until Wednesday.
   The hearing, which was to be held Monday in Delaware Chancery
Court before Vice Chancellor Jack B. Jacobs, will be held instead
at 2 p.m. EDT Wednesday, a spokesman for the court confirmed.
   Bass has offered to acquire Macmillan for $1.9 billion, but the
company responded by announcing a restructuring that will separate
Macmillan's publishing and information services into two public
companies as well as pay shareholders a special dividend.
   Earlier this month Jacobs granted Bass's request for a temporary
injunction blocking the restrucurting.
   At Wednesday's hearing, Jacobs will hear arguments concerning a
preliminary injunction, which would void the proposed restructuring.
