<HEAD>Steel Output Fell 1.5 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production fell to 1.819 million tons in
the week ended June 25, a decrease of 1.5 percent from the previous
week's 1.846 million tons, the American Iron and Steel Institute
reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 84.9 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 86.1 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
49.089 million net tons, an increase of 22.4 percent from the
40.103 million net tons in the previous year.
