   A 24-year-old junior securities analyst for
Morgan Stanley & Co. has been accused with a Hong Kong businessman
of making $19 million in illegal profits in what the government is
calling the second-largest insider trading case ever.
   The Securities and Exchange Commission on Monday filed a civil
complaint against Stephen Wang Jr., an analyst in Morgan Stanley's
mergers and acquisitions department. Also named in the complaint
was Fred. C. Lee, a Hong Kong businessman who allegedly traded on
the information supplied by Wang.
</TEXT>
